    "created_at": "2017-12-06T23:27:50Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-12-06T23:27:50Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "We debated this issue at length on a number of different occasions over the past few months and explored various designs and considered feedback in https://groups.google.com/forum/?utm_medium=email&utm_source=footer#!msg/grpc-io/0hmnCpCKIUk/H7EFeONDCgAJ and settled on the following design:\r\n\r\n> Add a `ServicerContext.abort(code, details)` method that the user can call when they want to terminate an RPC with a non-OK status.  This method raises an exception, thereby terminating the execution of the handler immediately without it needing to return anything. The gRPC runtime recognizes this exception value and responds to the client with the specified status code and details.\r\n"
  },
